This year began in the studio making Newfound Oxygen and is ending with test pressings and printed jackets at my doorstep (more on that later). Self-funding/releasing/distributing is a bitch and a half for 10,000 reasons but I love it. The details and the logistics and the pain. Every single thing leaves my hands and goes directly into yours. Disgusting in a pandemic, I know, but that connection means the world to me. Thanks yall. So excited to share this thing soon.
Newfound Oxygennnn

Happy slappy January everyone. So excited to share I’ll be playing @npr @mountainstage Jan 22. Holy smokes. See you soon, Charleston-area vegan options 🤙 
📸: @gregchow

Many things to share next week including ⚖️ The Balance ⚖️
📸 @mikedempseyy

Well well well. You THOUGHT I was done making keychains from defective (unused!) night guards from my former subscription. Pre-save The Balance and you’ll be entered to win this timeless, elegant and frankly gorgeous keychain. Apologies to everyone who can’t unsee this.
The Balance next Tuesday 🕳

The Balance coming on Tuesday

👋 to my cash-only “stunt” coordinator @mikedempseyy
The Balance and a few more things tomorrow yall! Pre-save before 9p for a chance to win that tasty tasty night guard.

The Balance is about getting knocked down a peg and setting boundaries along the way forward. Or at least trying to? Whatever. Life is slippery. I’m so proud of this song and even more proud of the video at the moment, as it was finished about 6 hours ago through sheer will and imbalance in every area of @ravishankara’s life for the past week to get this thing completed on schedule, and beautifully. He demands that you enjoy it, and you know what? So do I 😘

I finally made shirts. Magnetic Poetry? Why not! Super limited quantities of everything. It’s here and it’s gone babyyy. All on @bandcamp

The Newfound Oxygen album release show will be on Mar 15 at @dynastytypewriter, one of my favorite venues in LA. It will be early, it will be seated, it will be CIVILIZED. The album will have been out for nearly a month before the show because I want you to have a relationship with it going in. So you can sing along, sure, but also not fail the quiz that will be given at the end of the evening. Pens will be provided. Tickets are on sale now.
gotta learn the balance yall
2 weeks til Newfound Oxygen! If you’re interested in ordering anything, today’s a good day on this @bandcamp friday. Also shirts are restocked in all sizes, those went quick! Thanks yall love you.

One more week = one more raffle 😎 This time we have one excellent item and 3 just-okay *collectibles* from The Balance video. Pre-save Newfound Oxygen on your streaming platform to enter and omg good luck!!!
I should mention vinyl has landed 🎯
Surprise! Newfound Oxygen (the song) is out now 🛫🫁🥼🧪👩‍🔬 🥽 🛬

On behalf of everyone here at the Steady Holiday Fulfillment Center, thank you for pre-ordering Newfound Oxygen. Your stuff is aboard the Pony Express right tf now. Special thanks to @krisirvingchen for beginning the vinyl pressing process with me in an email dated Apr 29, 2022. These things take time yall. Special thanks pt. 2 to @citizenvinyl for excellently pulling off a high-risk, high-baby-poop-potential color combination. If you haven’t ordered your Tobleroone Float®️yet, I assure you there’s no time like the present. Thank you again, everyone. This all means so much to me.

Wanna roast the Newfound Oxygen video with me tonight on YouTube at 9p PT? Maybe like 8:45? I always forget that in the digital world a Friday release actually means Thursday 9p (my time). So let’s watch the video and chit chat and then I’m gonna sleep for like 3 days. Album is out tonight!!

Newfound Oxygen: A tale of rogue science, starting over and lift-off. 

Directed by: @ravishankara 
Director of Photography: @omgdlb

Sound Design: @stuffbydanny 
Color Producer: Esther Minitser
Camera everything: @otm_cameralighting

These photos were the first draft of album artwork. I knew we could beat it. 

I started writing Newfound Oxygen in August 2021. Can’t Find A Way came first. After a few more songs took shape, I realized that LP4 would be an extension of Take The Corners Gently - still working through things like how to live in the world, and be at peace with the good and bad. These topics are evergreen to me. Because they keep changing as I keep changing. I’ll probably write about them forever. Get… used to it?

What my songs mean to me changes too, so I’d rather not explain anything hard and fast. I wanna hand over the keys so you can have your own experience. Take em for a spin. Listen through your phone speaker! Jk don’t be savage.

I think of Steady Holiday as a micro-operation in pretty much every way, until I pull back and realize how many people I’m surrounded by who are simply down to party. Who say yes, over and over. Collaborators and friends and fans, both recent and ride-or-dies.

The following are the folks who have touched Newfound Oxygen, but there are so many more of you who have impacted Steady Holiday (and my life) with your support and attention and love over the years, and for that I want to say thank you forever. You know who you are. 

Without further ado…. Newfound Oxygen!

Giving away this @yamaha_guitars one week from today at @dynastytypewriter. Doors at 6:30, Steady Holiday at 7:30 (no opening act). I’m not kidding ok I wanna be in bed by 10.

Next Wednesday. So unbelievably excited to share these songs live. I got a lot of friends coming together with their various and/or questionable talents to celebrate Newfound Oxygen. I don’t play often, but when I do, you are 100% guaranteed to leave with delight and more questions than you came with. See you there 😎

Added an “art” exhibit to the show tomorrow at @dynastytypewriter. Some tickets still available. Reminder that this is an early bird event (we play at 7:30). No rock and roll bullshit. See you so soon 🐓😎

Thank you to everyone who put this show on its feet. Thank you to everyone who came and participated, and to Tyson for walking up to me and asking “will you sign my Horrible Bosses shirt?” It really made my night. The whole night made my night. Let’s do it again soon.

This one’s bittersweet. It’s about that sinking feeling of misalignment in a relationship. One that has love, and history, and yet the path forward isn't exactly clear. 

It came together as easy as breaking up is hard. @removador and I assembled this little ditty from different sides of the country, and @invisible__island helped us take it over the finish line. Hope you enjoy ❤️

In this video, Dre Babinski, aka @steadyholiday talks about her journey as a musician, the people and experiences that inspired her, and accepting that everything changes - including herself.
